<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12059b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12059b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12059b"> 59(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> oubliettes = latrines / or charniers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Certains r&eacute;duits ont &eacute;t&eacute; qualifi&eacute;s d&apos;oubliettes. Ce n&apos;&eacute;taient que des latrines ou encore des charniers. On comprend que les assi&eacute;g&eacute;s ne pouvaient jeter par-dessus les remparts les corps de ceux qui mouraient, moines et hommes d&apos;armes, &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur du Mont. On les faisait dispara&icirc;tre dans des trous dissimul&eacute;s, que la passion politique a transform&eacute;s en in pace abominables! <br><font color="green">[Some of the redoubts were called dungeon. They were no more than latrines or else mass graves. We understand that the besieged could not throw beyond the ramparts the bodies of those who had died inside the Mont, monks or soldiers. They were made to disappear in hidden holes that the political passions had transformed into abominable in pace!&rdquo;]</font> <small> &Eacute;tienne Dupont, <a name="SMIN" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SMIN"><cite title="source">Le Mont Saint-Michel Inconnu</cite></a> (1912) 204n2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
